post_text:
Today is the last day of Grab & Go Meals for the COVID-19 School Closure. We've assembled more than 25,000 meals since our start back on March 24!

Thanks to all who came out to get meals, and special thanks to the many volunteers who helped hand out meals each day. We couldn't have done it without you!

Today's lunch entrees include:
-Sunbutter & Jelly Sandwich plus Yogurt OR String Cheese
-Chicken Nuggets & Potato Wedges OR Sweet Potato Fries
-Assortment that may include Calzone OR Cheesy Breadsticks OR Sloppy Joe OR BBQ Pork OR Hamburger on Bun

See you in the Fall!

post_text:
Today Iowa Governor Reynolds extended school closure for the remainder of the 19-20 school year. GHV administration encourages our parents and students to keep engaging in the continuous learning activities being provided by our GHV teachers. While this announcement does mean GHV students will not be returning to classes as usual for this school year, there are several details to be determined.
More information will be shared in the coming days regarding how GHV will proceed for the remainder of this school year, as well as how and when the school year will officially close.

post_text:
GHV Parents, Guardians, and Students,
Please join us in spreading some cheer! On Wednesday, April 1st, at 3:30pm, GHV staff will be joining together to participate in a caravan wave to our students! Staff will be traveling through the streets in the Garner community first and then traveling to Ventura! If you are concerned that the caravan may not pass by your home, we plan to be sure to caravan down the Homecoming route in Garner. In Ventura, we will be traveling East on old Hwy.18 and taking a left on Main St. Please keep in mind we will be modeling social distancing and encourage you and your students to do the same. Please have your students remain on the sidewalk and wave! We hope this will be a fun and uplifting event for our students, staff, parents, and communities!
If you have questions, please feel free to contact:
Tracy Smeby - tsmeby@ghvschools.org
Jaci Hayes - jhayes@ghvschools.org
Katrina Klooster - kklooster@ghvschools.org
Kelsey Edwards - kedwards@ghvschools.org
We miss you all! -GHV Staff

post_text:
Beginning Tuesday, March 24, 2020
GHV Grab & Go Meals
11:30 am - 12:30 pm
-Pick up locations: GHV Elem & GHV Middle School
-Meals will be picked up curbside
-Available on a first come, first serve basis
-No eating on site
-Free to all children ages 1-18 living in households where at least one child attends GHV School District
-One lunch & one breakfast provided at each Grab & Go
-Each child must be present in order to receive a meal (if you bring 2 children, 2 lunches and 2 breakfast meals will be served)
-Questions can be directed to Kathy Zobrist, GHV School Nutrition Director, or to building principals
Kathy Zobrist: kzobrist@ghvschools.org
Jim Haag: jhaag@ghvschools.org
Debra Steenhard: dsteenhard@ghvschools.org
Michael Meyering: mmeyering@ghvschools.org
